1
00:00:00,816 --> 00:00:04,396
Want to make your accessibility statement page easier for your customers to find?

2
00:00:04,966 --> 00:00:11,816
In this video, I'll show you exactly how to add a page to your Shopify menu so your customers can access it effortlessly.

3
00:00:12,686 --> 00:00:17,866
If you're new to Shopify or just getting started, don't worry.

4
00:00:17,866 --> 00:00:19,636
I'll walk you through each step clearly.

5
00:00:20,096 --> 00:00:25,936
By the end of this video, you'll know how to link any page to your store's navigation, making browsing intuitive for everyone.

6
00:00:26,586 --> 00:00:30,956
Step 1: From your Shopify dashboard, click on Content, then select Menus.

7
00:00:31,436 --> 00:00:33,766
This is where you manage all your store's menus.

8
00:00:34,226 --> 00:00:41,206
Step 2: Choose the menu you want to edit; for this video, we'll use the footer menu, which appears at the bottom of your store.

9
00:00:41,206 --> 00:00:43,476
Click on it to see the existing menu items.

10
00:00:43,896 --> 00:00:50,496
Step 3: Click on Add menu item, enter the name of the new item, for example, Accessibility Statement.

11
00:00:50,776 --> 00:00:58,826
Step 4: Link this menu item to the page you want it to lead to. Since this is an accessibility statement, select your accessibility statement page.

12
00:00:59,106 --> 01:01:21,556
Step 5: Click Save to update the menu. Step 6: Go to your online store and click up here to view your store, you'll see the accessibility statement page successfully added to your footer menu, ready for your customers to access easily.

13
01:01:21,556 --> 01:01:24,256
Now your Shopify menu is updated.

14
01:01:24,256 --> 01:01:27,516
And your customers can navigate your store more easily.

15
01:01:27,516 --> 01:01:30,986
Don't forget to try it yourself and make your store even more user-friendly.